                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/34<hi rend="superscript">5/12</hi>:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-29T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 29, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>89. My telegram No. 79, June 16, 10 [<hi rend="italic">11</hi>] p.m. Will the
                    Department please inform me as early as possible the method and date preferred
                    for further consultations with Peru? I make this request in order to be able to
                    put the Peruvian officials on notice well in advance. Otherwise I fear they may
                    not be properly prepared.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
